				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After looking as some of the crap on this form, something to think about before you post
<br />

<br />
We get the best pets, its simple stop whining for our pet to do the dps of time geared rouge our pets are better unbuffed and left alone , and buffed and being supported , when you factor in  there other spells and melee for bl it is about equal.
<br />
 
<br />
Our pet is only 40% of our dmg output  most ppl who whine about this want about a 30 -70% dps boost for our pets 40% of our dmg *30 % lacking =12 %  dps lower then we “should be at” (please notice the quotes)  be now keep in mind that we are a solo class ,  because we are not 100%-90% group dependent we should NOT bring as much to a group ( or raid for that matter ) as a rouge, cleric , enchanter war exc.
<br />
 Try not to post omg our pets sukers make our lvl 4 pet have 10 * then dmg output of a perfectly geared rouge with max aa’s and 10 * the tank ability of a perfectly geared warrior with full aa’s.
<br />

<br />
We do not need root; when clerics get invis then say we need root.
<br />

<br />
Druid dps comes fully from there nukes ours comes 60 % nukes 40 % pet so we out dmg them. If they have equal or slightly better nukes our pet more then makes up for it while they get snare ports and heals instead, a trade off not a dramatic imbalance, which favors grouping greatly.
<br />

<br />
That covers most of it, feel free to post add on or xalmat  post a final version of something like this.
<br />

<br />
A example of a good class balance idea <a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target="_blank">http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html</a>
<br />

