			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Please note that this is the class balance forum, where people who think we are *not* perfectly balanced, suggest things.
<br />

<br />
Yes, there are some really moronic threads on here (though at least the second one you singled out is by no means a poorly thought out or unbalancing idea) but there are also some valuable threads.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>shadowscream wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">After looking as some of the crap on this form, something to think about before you post </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Fair enough, I'm with you up to this point.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We get the best pets</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
debatable.  best for what?  best for dps? cause that's wrong, unless you mean best dps unbuffed.  best at tanking with a cleric healing?  sure.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> its simple stop whining for our pet to do the dps of time geared rouge</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I've seen exactly one person, ever, express that our pets should be better than a time geared <span style="font-style: italic">rogue</span>, in a log of a duel between their DPoC pet and a time rogue where they were surprised by the outcome.  In case you missed that thread, which is doubtful since you mentioned the same scenario, everyone else on the board laughed at the original poster.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> our pets are better unbuffed and left alone , and buffed and being supported , when you factor in  there other spells and melee for bl it is about equal.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Really not sure what all you're saying here.  It's not a continuation of above, despite lack of intervening punctuation, and it's unclear whether you're talking about pets, or comparative agregate DPS for mages and beastlords.  If BL dps is about equal to mine, there's a problem.  
<br />
 
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Our pet is only 40% of our dmg output</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This is impossible to say.  For me, it's probably about right, if not a little high.  For high end raiders with ancient nukes, ft20 and clicky mana regens on top of huge manapools, 20% manapres and 45% nuke focus, 40% is probably way high.  For the general populus at 65, it looks low, honestly.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">most ppl who whine about this want about a 30 -70% dps boost for our pets 40% of our dmg *30 % lacking =12 %  dps lower then we “should be at” (please notice the quotes)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Your math is difficult to follow.  You begin with a large range (30-70%), and then state that we are 12% lower than people are requesting.  Seems to me that we are 12% to 28% behind where people want to be, following your logic in keeping pets at the same percentage of our DPS they have fallen to.  
<br />

<br />
I can't pretend to speak for everybody.  Hell, I can't even pretend to have been 50 when they raised the level cap to 60, but I can say that my pet was MUCH more than 40% of my DPS until the 50+ pets. Back when pets took experience, a solo mage had to outdamage his pet on each mob.  This was often HARD to do.  Now, I can do more damage than my pet will ever do against a mob in one convenient 6.5k crit.  This is because nuke inflation outpaced pet inflation.  Some people are still annoyed by this.  They like the total DPS we output, but dislike that we have to nuke to do 60% of it. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> now keep in mind that we are a solo class ,  because we are not 100%-90% group dependent we should NOT bring as much to a group ( or raid for that matter ) as a rouge, cleric , enchanter war exc.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
we are?  where did I miss that memo?  
<br />

<br />
ability to solo != solo class.
<br />

<br />
enchanters can solo as well as or better than we can in many places.  many many many "utility" classes solo better than we do as a pure DPS class, which is fine by me really, but a far cry from what we were at release.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Try not to post omg our pets sukers make our lvl 4 pet have 10 * then dmg output of a perfectly geared rouge with max aa’s and 10 * the tank ability of a perfectly geared warrior with full aa’s.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
i've never, ever, seen a post that asked for either pet DPS of a rogue or tankage of a warrior.  My level 66 pet does significantly more damage and tanks better than a level 65 bazarr equipped &lt;50aa tank, and that's enough for me.
<br />

<br />
That said, omg our lvl 1 pets suxors.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We do not need root; when clerics get invis then say we need root.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I've never seen anyone say we need root.  I have seen many people say that it would be nice to have, which I agree with.  
<br />

<br />
Also, much like clerics are one of two casting classes that do not get invis (their hybrid, paladins, being the other), we remain one of three casting classes without root (the others being Shadowknights and Beastlords, who are both hybrids.)
<br />

<br />
Also of note is that we are the *only* int caster without roots and runes.
<br />

<br />
That said, no, we don't need them.  We have other methods to get around the use of them.  Of course, of the two most common methods, one is an exploit, and the other is "don't get hit."
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Druid dps comes fully from there nukes ours comes 60 % nukes 40 % pet so we out dmg them. If they have equal or slightly better nukes our pet more then makes up for it while they get snare ports and heals instead, a trade off not a dramatic imbalance, which favors grouping greatly.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well said.  I have no problem with druids having roughly equivalent nukes.  However, it is exceedlingly cheesy that currently they are <span style="font-style: italic">precisely</span> equal to ours.  Also, back before the minor minor minor retunings they did, druid nukes often did 10 or 20 damage more than magician nukes, while taking 5 less mana.
<br />

<br />
The <span style="font-style: italic">only</span> reason for this anyone has ever suggested to me was to piss magicians off.  In practice, the difference was negligable, but in theory, it was no less offensive.  It worked, and mages are still upset about it, despite druids rarely getting the chance to show off their nuking talents.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
