<br />

<br />
IMO pets should be closer to 70% of our damage output.  When an enchanter charms, a pet is typically 100% of his dps, but it tends to outdamage both the magician and his summoned pet put together.  As far as soloability, that depends on where you want to solo, and what pets you have access to.  For some strange reason, SOE decided to make our PoP and OoW Earth pets (the de facto solo pet for most magicians) the most difficult pets to obtain.  This tends to make us more group dependent until we get the ever elusive earthie.
<br />

<br />
I don't need my pets to outdamage rogues and out-tank warriors.  I do want a pet that will allow me to contribute significant dps in a group before nukes are added to the pot, and can tank well enough to solo in most level-appropriate zones.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We do not need root; when clerics get invis then say we need root.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
