<br />
That depends.  If a druid charms a mob, the dps figures change somewhat, but the druid has a lot of tools to protect himself from a potential charm break, making charm dps quite viable.  In addition, druids get several AA legs up for both their caster and their priest side.
<br />

<br />
Magicians do okay most of the time, but there are definitely times when the odds seem against us.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
