Are you really trying to say that the best mage pets are only slightly better than beastlord pets, in regards to DPS and mitigation?  If so, then you really do not have a high level magician.  After the changes several months ago, mage pets out-mitigate warders by a very large margin.  Slow helps us out in this regards (but hey, unless you are soloing, your mobs will most likely be slowed as well.  Plus we are comparing pets, right?).  Your most damage pet easily outdamages a warder as well.  Don't  make your pets sound gimp.  They are not when compared to warders or necro pets.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I am saying that the differences are generally small.  Our backstabber pet's dps is roughly equivalent to a necromancer's backstabber pet's dps.  Our best tanking pet is somewhat more resilient than a warder, but hardly worlds apart.  Frontal pet dps among the pet classes is more or less in the same ballpark, with the magicians on top, but once again, not by a boatload.
<br />

<br />
My point is simply that pet dps is not quite what it should be, and in my opinion should constitute 70% of our damage potential.  I don't have a lot of complaints about mitigation, except to say that versus level-appropriate content (unslowed, of course), I am forced to chain.  I should be able to do more damag before the pet needs to be chained, without risking aggro.
<br />

<br />
Naturally this is an opinion, and subject for debate.  I am just giving my two cents.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
