			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't agree with the premise that armor has only a minor effect. I *know* from experience that an armored mage pet tanks "dramatically" better than unarmored one (unfocused of course). At level 61 before I got my dpoc, I'd duo my then level 53 shaman with my 61 mage in PoN. WoX unarmored required chain healing from the shaman and nuke/heal cycle from the mage to stay up after slow/cripple. WoX with just summoned plate, tanked well enough that the shammy could drop a couple dots, while maintaining the same mana levels. 
<br />

<br />
I don't have logs, but what I do recall is that armor increased the kill rate from 8 mobs / cycle to 10. 20% more exp is a dramatic improvement.
<br />

<br />
Aqui<br />_________________<br />Aquilistor Portavendor
